						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Wall of a well called the Nīm-Bāwri, near Gol Gumbaz.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">A.D. 1580.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in Nāgarī characters is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1502, Vikrama, Chaitra śu 1, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1580, March 16, Wednesday.</hi> It begins with a Sanskrit verse in praise of the holy place <hi rend="bold">Prayāga</hi> and records in <hi rend="italic">Marāṭhi</hi> the construction of a well.</p>						

